# Golden Thread refresh

When you finish work that changes any traceability input:

- `tasks.md` (task status, new tasks, or `Traces:` IDs)
- PRD / spec IDs
- `@covers` annotations in Swift source
- AC-prefixed unit test names (`test_AC_*`)

Then before marking the task complete:

1. Run `bash scripts/check-traceability.sh --refresh` from the repo root.
   - Gate 2 check (must pass)
   - Regenerates `specs/001-mvp/coverage.md` and `coverage.svg` (commit before hiring or release pushes)
   - Optionally updates the local Cursor canvas **HomesFlow Golden Thread — Coverage** (outside git)

2. If Gate 2 fails, fix gaps or add pending test tasks — do not leave untracked ACs.

3. CI enforces the golden thread, not coverage file freshness — no need to regenerate on every push.

Canvas path (override with `GOLDEN_THREAD_CANVAS`):

`~/.cursor/projects/Users-rik-Developer-HomesFlow/canvases/golden-thread-coverage.canvas.tsx`
